<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB00062</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT STRENGTHENING THE POWERS OF THE NATIONAL TELECOMMUNICATIONS COMMISSION, AMENDING FOR THE PURPOSE REPUBLIC ACT NO. 7925, OTHERWISE KNOWN AS THE ꞌPUBLIC TELECOMMUNICATIONS POLICY ACT OF THE PHILIPPINESꞌ</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SHORT TITLE : Strengthening The Powers Of The National Telecommunications Commission, Amending For The Purpose Republic Act No. 7925</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Seeks to amend Republic Act No. 7925 to expand the National Telecommunications Commission (NTCs) powers and capacity to regulate TELCOS and other industry–related entities. Strengthens the quasi-judicial functions of the National Telecommunications Commission (NTC) as the main regulator of  the Philippine Telecommunications Industry, and improved the delivery of public telecommunication services. </td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>YAP, VICTOR A.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-07-01</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Vergara (000 2019-09-12)</td><td>2. Agabas (000 2019-11-13)</td><tr><td>3. Espino (000 2019-12-05)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON INFORMATION AND COMMUNICATIONS TECHNOLOGY ON 2019-07-23</td></tr></table>